=Description=

"After the success of our 'Take Back The Web' event in Brighton, which shared online activism skills amongst technologists and campaigners, we have formed ourselves as the 'Web Activist Collective'. We have big plans, and part of those plans involves this blog. Over the coming weeks, you'll get to meet us all, as well as finding out about how things like blogs and wikis can help you change the world. We'll also give our thoughts on how we think the internet is being taken over by big business, and why its time to reclaim the web."
(http://webactivistcollective.org/?q=node/1)

